Product name: Authentic Tuareg Fulani Earrings
Description:
The gold that Fulani craftsmen used was one of many goods that passed through this once- thriving trade center. As the flow of goods slowed to a trickle once the Portuguese established trade ports along the coast, Fulani craftsmen adapted their skills to more easily acquired metals such a brass. Today the town of just under 40,000 people has an agrarian economy, but Fulani metal smiths and jewelers still ply their trade in Djenne's markets.

Perfect: The piece of jewelry has no visible flaws and no signs of wear.
Excellent: The piece of jewelry has evidence of wear, such as uneven or matte finish, especially on the backs of earrings.
Great: The piece of jewelry has small flaws that are not usually noticeable during wear. These flaws could include light scratches of imitation pearls, light scuffs on stones, or light marks on the metal's finish.
Good: The piece of jewelry is completely wearable with working hardwear; however, the stones may be yellowing or beginning to turn grey (dark spots are visible looking into the stone), the wear may be more visible, and there may be light chipping.
Fair: The piece of jewelry has visible damage that may include dark stones, missing stones, or broken parts.

Product name: 100 Antique Marbles, 1920's-1950's,  Peltier, Akro, Vitro, Master, Marble King, Etc.  Worth Hundreds of Dollars
Description:
This listing is for 100 old marbles, generally 5/8" size.  Most of these will be from the late 1950's or older, some possibly back even to the 1800's.  Many, if not most of these will be in one or more of the various marble price guides for as much as 2 to 8 EACH!  That means that technically, in each lot you are getting several hundred dollars worth of marbles here.  However, they are common enough patterns the experienced collectors already have them and don't look at these.  So at shows I wholesale these out for 1 each and go through hundreds of them.  Home decorators and artists love these, as do children or beginning collectors, because they are so colorful and varied.  I've even had fellow marble dealers pick up a couple hundred at a time.
Just about anything could potentially show up here: Peltier baseballs, Akro corkscrews, Vitro tri-colors, dyed clays, Peltier Rainbo's, Marble King multi-colors, Master Made Sunbursts, Champion Jr.'s, unglazed chinas, Vitro Helmets, Banana-style and caged cat's eyes, slags, hybrid cat's eyes, older patches and brushed, Peltier sunsets, older All-Reds or Blackies, West Virginia swirls from a number of companies.....you get the idea.  Anything old might be found.
Pictures are just examples (plate not included).  I'll simply pick the next 100 marbles out of my bins.  Most will be mint or near mint condition, though in large lots like this you are bound to get an occasional chip or manufacturing flaw.
I'll drop the price down to 65 for each lot, multiple lots available.

Product name: Canvas bank deposit money bag, canvas bank bag, vintage night deposit canvas money bag with lock
Description:
Vintage canvas bank deposit bag
The bag can be dated 1960's because according to my research, the company name was changed to A. Rifkin & CO. and in 1972 the look was changed from the Arcolock to the #7 lock in order to provide a more secure lock.
The lock on this bag is marked A Rikin and Co. and is an Arcolock.
Made of canvas, the bag is from the Haverhill National Bank in Haverhill, Massachusetts. It measures 10 x 7 inches. The zipper works fine, the lock has signs of age with scuffs, scratches and some patina. I do not have a key.
The bag itself has signs of age with some fading and discoloring with no rips or tears. Also there are some scuffs on the leather patch by the lock.
I believe this would make a really great purse but I just do not have the energy in this time in life to do this and I probably will regret it.

Description:
This beautiful plate titled “Scarlett’s Shopping Spree“ was issued between 1991 to 1993 by the Bradford Exchange and is issue #8 of 12 for the series “Critic’s Choice: Gone with the Wind” Bradex 84-G20-41.  The 8-1/2” diameter plate has gold edging and was produced and fired by W. S. George Fine China.  The back includes all the information about the plate.  The artwork painting was rendered by Paul Jennis authorized by Turner Home Entertainment.  Mr. Jennis beautifully captures the characters, events and scenes from the film.  It is marked Plate No 2558B and is suitable for framing, to use with a plate hanger or stand.  It is not suitable for serving food.
The Gone with the Wind academy award winning film was released in 1939 and produced from the novel that won the 1937 Pulitzer Prize for Fiction written by Margaret Mitchell.  This extraordinary movie will commemorate its 75th Anniversary in 2014. 
Condition – Pristine with no cracks or chips.  Has been kept in a sealed tote with no use.  Comes in the original box with all collector tags.  If you collect Gone With the Wind, this would be a wonderful addition to your collection or to fill any missing pieces you may need.

Product name: 17thc Nicholas Dorigny Antique portrait 1684 head study sanguine drawing antique bearded man
Description:
Antique portrait European School 18th/ 19th-century head study of a bearded man in profile,
 
Possibly by Nicholas Dorigny (French, born circa 1657–1746)
Sanguine drawing
 
A rather fabulous antique drawing which I bought years ago (I'm currently selling some of my personal items). I love the colour & quality of the drawing, in particular, the cross hatching & the wavy lines depicting the hair. Indistinct signature on laid paper, unidentified watermark, but I have been informed by a very helpful Etsy person that it probably dates to 1684 & is by the artist Nicholas Dorigny.
See https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nicolas_Dorigny 
" In 1711 he was invited to England by Queen Anne to engrave the Cartoons of Raphael at Hampton Court, which he finished in 1719, and in the following year he was knighted by King George I. While he was in England he painted some portraits of the nobility, but with no great success. He returned to France in 1725, and was received into the Academy in the same year. Product name: Pet Revolution™ 16" Ultra Silent Deluxe Chinchilla Wheel, Free Organic Special Treat with every purchase!
Description:
***Very proud Buffalo Mtn Curios was named #75 out of top 100 Etsy Pet Sellers! What an honor! <3 We work very hard to give you quality products for your furbabies. :) <3***
*New and Improved! Brand new roller blade wheels are in! They are bigger and better to ensure even more longevity of your lil one's wheel!*
Every order comes with a special treat for your furbaby! Organic chew sticks from the awesome Cherokee Forest Woods Co! They are a great local company, the only place we trust for our chin's treats! <3 <3 
The absolute BEST Chinchilla wheel you will find! I painstakingly designed the most QUIET and SAFEST Chinchilla exercise wheel that I could and after a lot of trial and error this is my final result. We tried just about every other wheel out there from 10 name brand to overpriced "silent" plastic wheels, flying saucer and even the top of line spinner wheel. They all had one quirk or another that we didn't like, usually they sounded like a small freight train was barreling through the house! 
Width of pan is just shy of 4".
The wheel itself is made from rolled galvanized steel which will be sturdy and will not rust or corrode, The bearing is a sealed bearing which is designed for high r.p.m, high speed applications so it requires no grease or oil and will last for years. All of the mounting hardware is pure 18-8 stainless steel so NO RUST!! We only get the best, top quality stainless steel hardware.
On the back of the pan is 2 galvanized mounting brace plates securely installed to provide superior stability as compared to any other wheel handmade or commercially available. The plates eliminate the possibility of any "flex" in the wheel or on the cage which will prolong the life of the wheel as well as your cage. 
We have also tried to minimize the space between the cage and the wheel itself, so the chin can not get trapped. We have also made this wheel as lightweight as physically possible! This wheel will NOT break your Ferret Nation cages because of weight issues!
Disclaimers: These pans do come with a sticky coating from the factory for their protection. My husband carefully cleans each pan to get most of it off, as a tiny little bit does have to stay on to protect the metal. So do not be alarmed if you happen to feel anything when inspecting carefully. <3
Also, please be aware that if you are putting the wheel on a bottom floor, where they can pee down on it, an easy solution would be to put a ledge above the mechanism. Animals constantly peeing onto the bearing could cause it to gunk up and start to make noise.
We also found a great solution to those flimsy cages. If you take a solid piece of wood or metal and place it the width of the cage (from corner to corner) that will help stabilize your wheel! We can always make one for you if you are unable to. :)
:D Happy running! :D
We can also accommodate all your custom hammock, tube and ledge needs! Just message us! We look forward to serving you. <3

Description:

Extremely soft, premium minky cuddle weighted blanket made for children or adults with special needs such as Sensory Processing Disorder, ADHD, Autism, Anxiety, PTSD, Restless Leg Syndrome and much more.  Weighted blankets can be used by anyone and everyone. The super soft material along with added weight helps calm and relax you for a good nights rest or to unwind at the end of the day.  It can also be used to help calm children and/or adults who are experiencing stressful situations.
XSM Weighted Blanket: 32"x42"
Small Weighted Blanket: 32'" x 56". 
Medium Weighted Blanket:  38"x 62" 
Large Weighted Blanket: 51"x72" 
XLG Weighted Blanket: 59"x82" (approx.)
Weights are custom made to fit individual person. Typical weights are 10% of the persons body weight plus 1 pound as per Occupational Therapists suggestion. We use a combination of low watt Nostalgic Era and incandescent bulbs in each chandelier. They vary in size, shape and style. They’re the perfect complement to any vintage industrial, rustic modern, or contemporary décor.
SOCKETS 
All sockets are UL approved, medium E-26 base. There are a variety of finishes available. Prices vary. See the attached chart for a reference, and message us with any requests.
MOUNTING / CONNECTION

Flush Mount: Let us know if you are planning to flush mount the chandelier: we will pre-drill the holes and supply the necessary hardware, toggle bolts. Please note you will need a minimum of 2” clearance from the ceiling to the canopy.
UL LISTING
Our chandeliers are made with UL listed parts, but the chandelier itself does not have a UL rating at this time. 
REPLACEMENT BULBS
We do sell replacement bulbs. You can purchase an extra set with your chandelier to save on shipping. Please message us for a special listing.  LED bulbs are also available.
NOTE
Each light is handcrafted and no two are exactly alike. Every effort is made to match the dimensions, color tone, and finished texture as closely as possible.

Description:
Abundance -Fertility Goddess Statue Doula Midwife Gift Mother Earth Sculpture Pagan Buddhist Altar Birth Art Blessingway Womb blessing
The theme fertility is common to all cultures of the world. Inspired by the goddess of fertility, these pieces are steeped Symbolism. A feminine figure representing this theme - either sculpted in wood or clay - was always paid homage no matter the culture in question. It is only in our western world that we forget to honour the feminine principle as cultures of old did. This principle was honoured for its influence over aspects such as arable land, vegetation, creativity, family, health, wealth and abundance. By focusing on the Symbolism of the sculpture, tribal members were able to manifest fertility in their own lives.
My reproduction Abundance sculptures are created from my original, hand cast and hand finished in my studio. They are filled with this Symbolism, created with me paying homage to this principle long forgotten in our modern society.
A beautiful gift for a doula / midwife, or as symbolism for bringing Abundance into your life.

Product name: Terrarium Kits for Children, Butterfly and Insect Decor, Child's Room, Educational Activity, Craft Kit, DIY Kit, Science, Nature, Eco-Friend
Description:
Learn about five different butterfly and insect specimens with this group of five adorable terrarium kits for children. The jars provided in this kit are acrylic, and therefore durable and safe for children.  The top of the jar has a magnifying feature which is fun for closer inspection of the insect.  The bugs and butterflies are dried/preserved so the displays last a long time! 
This group of five kits makes a great classroom display, a unique way to teach your homeschool group, or the best birthday party favors ever!  Unlike other educational activities or favors, these kits will not be tossed aside.  The end result is a beautiful display that will last for many years to come.  Each insect comes with educational information about its environment, favorite foods, or other fun facts.  In addition, our kits provide children with the opportunity to touch and explore nature up close.
This terrarium kit comes complete with everything you need to create this fun, real bug terrarium. Included in your kit:
- 5 acrylic jar (2 inch diameter by 3 inches tall), 
-moss
-dried floral elements
- 1 yellow phoebis butterfly - 55 mm wingspan,
- 1 red cymothoe sangaris butterfly - 55 mm wingspan
- 1 brown striped cyrestis Camillus butterfly - 40 mm wingspan
- 1 black horned beetle - 45 mm long
- 1 blue weevil bug - 25 mm long
-instructions 
Copy our design exactly, or get creative and add your own natural elements. This particular kit receives a difficulty rating of "easy" and is a fun project for children. 
Please note: These terrariums and bugs must be handled delicately. The terrariums are composed of dried floral elements as well as a real dried bug, so they must be kept away from moisture or prolonged direct sunlight, which can damage your terrarium and bug. When kept from moisture and sunlight, these terrariums will bring fun to your children for many years.
Our butterflies and bugs are imported from farms around the world, which raise these beautiful creatures and collect them once they have died. These farms promote the preservation of natural habitats and provide economic good to the countries in which they are located. Your purchase with the Amateur Naturalist is environmentally and economically friendly, as well as beautiful and fun!

Description:
Inspired by H. P. Lovecraft's Mythos, this D&D gaming Dice Box features the fearsome Cthulhu to store and protect your Dungeons and Dragons RPG Dice.
This little box in particular is designed to hold your dice, and if you've purchased one of our wooden deck boxes, they match perfectly! They easily fit a full set of 7 dice, plus a little extra wiggle room for one or two more.
We also have a slightly larger size that will allow you to triple the amount that can be stored.
Every box has a small strip of magnet that will help keep your slide lid closed when not in use. Each box also has the track that the slide rides on waxed
__________
**Important**
By default this deck comes with two different size options available at purchase.
Default Size: This size will hold approximately a full "set" of dice (D4, D6, D8, D10, %D10, D12, D20) plus at least 2 extra D20.
Taller Size: This size will hold roughly triple the amount of the default size.
NOTE: The amount of dice this box will actually hold will depend on the sizing of dice you use (If you use larger than average dice, it will hold less. If you use smaller than average dice it will hold more), AND what type of dice you're storing. (For instance, each box will hold a much greater amount of it's filled with only four sided dice.)
Each design is adjusted slightly for larger sizes, so you may notice a difference in the design as the sizes go up, but the overall aesthetic stays the same.
The dice pictured are not included in your purchase.
___________
How It's Made
The wood used is our wood of choice, Cherry Wood. Chosen for its sturdy durability while remaining easy for our machine to work with, as well as its gorgeous subtle red and golden luster when finished. Each product after engraving and cutting is sanded by hand to ensure the surface is smooth, then sealed with a clear varnish.
This listing is made to order, which means that you can expect from 3-10 business days for your order to be shipped.
___________
Customization
We're always happy to customize a listing any way you choose. Either send us a message or click "Request a custom order and have something made just for you." just above this listing's description to begin creating a custom order with us. The price of custom orders will depend on the complexity of the changes.
What sort of things can you customize? Anything! Want an image changed? Want more custom text options on other locations on the box? All of these are perfectly acceptable. For instance, if you'd rather have a flying spaghetti monster instead of a Chibi Cthulhu that's totally doable.

Product name: Boho Rings Unique Engagement Ring: raw stone ring, promise ring for her, alternative engagement ring, solitaire stone ring, raw quartz ring
Description:
Handcrafted copper ring, featuring a cluster of raw quartz crystal. 
Listed sizes are ready to ship the next business day. If you want a ring size that is not listed, select "US Custom Size" in the options.
Free shipping for any additional items purchased with this.
Store in the jewelry box with the tarnish resident tab that is provided with your order. 
The process: I start out with a handmade hammered ring, which gives the copper a lot of texture. I attach the stone to the ring, then sand the mounting to get the shape I want. The ring then goes through a really neat process called electroforming, where copper deposits onto the ring and around the base of the stone for about 12 hours. After waxing, sanding, and darkening the copper with a rich patina, the ring is finally complete! Long story short... a whole lot of time and love is put into this little beauty!

Edgar Rice Burroughs
was an American writer, best known for his creations of the jungle hero Tarzan and the heroic Mars adventurer John Carter, although he produced works in many genres.
Burroughs was born on September 1, 1875, in Chicago, Illinois (he later lived for many years in the suburb of Oak Park), the fourth son of businessman and Civil War veteran Major George Tyler Burroughs (1833–1913) and his wife Mary Evaline (Zieger) Burroughs (1840–1920). His middle name is from his paternal grandmother, Mary Rice Burroughs (1802–ca. 70).
Burroughs was educated at a number of local schools, and during the Chicago influenza epidemic in 1891, he spent a half year at his brother's ranch on the Raft River in Idaho. He then attended the Phillips Academy in Andover, Massachusetts, and then the Michigan Military Academy. Graduating in 1895, and failing the entrance exam for the United States Military Academy (West Point), he ended up as an enlisted soldier with the 7th U.S. Cavalry in Fort Grant, Arizona Territory. After being diagnosed with a heart problem and thus ineligible to serve, he was discharged in 1897.
After his discharge, Burroughs worked a number of different jobs. He drifted and worked on a ranch in Idaho. Then, Burroughs found work at his father's firm in 1899. He married his childhood sweetheart Emma Hulbert (1876-1944) in January 1900. In 1904, he left his job and worked less regularly, first in Idaho, then in Chicago.
By 1911, after seven years of low wages, he was working as a pencil sharpener wholesaler and began to write fiction. By this time, Burroughs and Emma had two children, Joan (1908–72), who would later marry Tarzan film actor James Pierce, and Hulbert (1909–91). During this period, he had copious spare time and he began reading many pulp fiction magazines. In 1929 he recalled thinking that
...if people were paid for writing rot such as I read in some of those magazines, that I could write stories just as rotten. As a matter of fact, although I had never written a story, I knew absolutely that I could write stories just as entertaining and probably a whole lot more so than any I chanced to read in those magazines.
Burroughs divorced Emma in 1934, and in 1935 he married former actress Florence Gilbert Dearholt, the former wife of his friend, Ashton Dearholt. Burroughs adopting the Dearholts' two children. He and Florence divorced in 1942.
Burroughs was in his late 60s and a resident of Hawaii at the time of the Japanese attack on Pearl Harbor. Despite his age, he applied for and received permission to become a war correspondent, becoming one of the oldest U.S. war correspondents during World War II. This period of his life is mentioned in William Brinkley's bestselling novel Don't Go Near the Water.
TARZAN
is a fictional character, an archetypal feral child raised in the African jungles by the Mangani great apes; he later experiences civilization only to largely reject it and return to the wild as a heroic adventurer. Created by Edgar Rice Burroughs, Tarzan first appeared in the novel Tarzan of the Apes (magazine publication 1912, book publication 1914), and subsequently in twenty-five sequels, three authorized books by other authors, and innumerable works in other media, both authorized and unauthorized.
Burroughs created an extreme example of a noble savage figure largely unalloyed with character flaws or faults. He is described as being Caucasian, extremely athletic, tall, handsome, and tanned, with grey eyes and long black hair. Emotionally, he is courageous, intelligent, loyal, and steadfast. He is presented as behaving ethically in most situations, except when seeking vengeance under the motivation of grief, as when his ape mother Kala is killed in Tarzan of the Apes, or when he believes Jane has been murdered in Tarzan the Untamed. He is deeply in love with his wife and totally devoted to her; in numerous situations where other women express their attraction to him, Tarzan politely but firmly declines their attentions. When presented with a situation where a weaker individual or party is being preyed upon by a stronger foe, Tarzan invariably takes the side of the weaker party. In dealing with other men, Tarzan is firm and forceful. With male friends, he is reserved but deeply loyal and generous. As a host, he is likewise, generous, and gracious. As a leader, he commands devoted loyalty.
In keeping with these noble characteristics, Tarzan's philosophy embraces an extreme form of "return to nature". Although he is able to pass within society as a civilized individual, he prefers to "strip off the thin veneer of civilization", as Burroughs often puts it. His preferred dress is a knife and a loincloth of animal hide, his preferred abode is any convenient tree branch when he desires to sleep, and his favored food is raw meat, killed by himself; even better if he is able to bury it a week so that putrefaction has had a chance to tenderize it a bit.
Tarzan's primitivist philosophy was absorbed by countless fans, amongst whom was Jane Goodall, who describes the Tarzan series as having a major influence on her childhood. She states that she felt she would be a much better spouse for Tarzan than his fictional wife, Jane, and that when she first began to live among and study the chimpanzees she was fulfilling her childhood dream of living among the great apes just as Tarzan did.
Rudyard Kipling's Mowgli has been cited as a major influence on Edgar Rice Burroughs' creation of Tarzan. Mowgli was also an influence for a number of other "wild boy" characters.
BURNE HOGARTH
was born in Chicago in 1911, the son of a housewife and a carpenter. His parents were immigrants from Eastern Europe. He displayed an early talent for drawing. His father saved these efforts and, some years later, presented them and the young Hogarth to the registrar at the Art Institute of Chicago. At age 12, Hogarth was admitted, thus embarking on a long formal education that took him through such institutions as Chicago's Crane College and Northwestern University, and New York City's Columbia University in New York City -- all the while, studying arts and sciences.
Due to his father’s premature death, Hogarth began work at age 15, when he became the assistant at the Associated Editors Syndicate and illustrated a series called Famous Churches of the World. He worked for several years as an editor and advertising artist. This work provided steady (and, by 1929, crucial) employment. In 1929, he drew his first comic strip, Ivy Hemmanhaw, for the Barnet Brown Company; in 1930 he drew Odd Occupations and Strange Accidents for Ledd Features Syndicate.
As the Great Depression worsened, Hogarth relocated to New York City at the urging of friends. He found employment with King Features Syndicate in 1934, drawing Charles Driscoll’s pirate adventure Pieces of Eight (1935). In 1936 came the assignment that catapulted Hogarth’s illustration career. With Tarzan, Hogarth brought together classicism, expressionism and narrative into a new form of dynamic, sequential art: the newspaper comic strip. Hogarth drew the Tarzan "Sunday (newspaper comic strip) page" for 12 years (1937–45; 1947–50). This work has been reprinted often, most recently by NBM Publishing.
TARZAN COMIC STRIPS
Tarzan of the Apes was adapted in newspaper strip form, in early 1929, with illustrations by Hal Foster. A full page Sunday strip began March 15, 1931 by Rex Maxon. Over the years, many artists have drawn the Tarzan comic strip, notably Burne Hogarth, Russ Manning, and Mike Grell. The daily strip began to reprint old dailies after the last Russ Manning daily (#10,308, which ran on 29 July 1972). The Sunday strip also turned to reprints circa 2000. Both strips continue as reprints today in a few newspapers and in Comics Revue magazine. NBM Publishing did a high quality reprint series of the Foster and Hogarth work on Tarzan in a series of hardback and paperback reprints in the 1990s.

The Tales of Beedle the Bard is a book of children's stories by British author J. K. Rowling. It purports to be the storybook of the same name mentioned in Harry Potter and the Deathly Hallows.
The book was originally produced in a limited edition of only seven copies, each handwritten and illustrated by J. K. Rowling.[3] One of them was offered for auction through Sotheby's in late 2007 and was expected to sell for £50,000.
It is described as a popular collection of Wizarding children's fairy tales, so that while Ron Weasley is familiar with the stories, Harry Potter and Hermione Granger had not previously heard of them due to their non-magical upbringing.
Rowling wrote five stories for the book. Product name: Rainer Maria Rilke, Poems,  limited edition handmade book
Description:
One of the most widely read and translated poets, the highly gifted and deeply spiritual Austrian/Czech poet Rainer Maria Rilke is often described as a “poet’s poet,” whose intense, introspective work influenced such fellow poets as Wallace Stevens, E. E. Cummings, Theodore Roethke, Randall Jarrell, Stephan Mitchell, and Robert Bly. 
Considered one of most significant literary figures of the early twentieth century, the first translations of Rilke began appearing in American newspapers as early as 1914, with the first book collection of his poems, translated by Jessie Lamont, published in 1918. This is a limited edition of the compete Lamont text, Rainer Maria Rilke: Poems, with the original introduction and a selection of the poet’s best known works, including: “Autumn,” “Moonlight Night,” “The Panther,” “I Live My Life in Circles,” and “Offering.” 
A handmade book, limited to a numbered edition of fifty, the text is set in Weiss with titles in Wellsbrook Initials. Pages and endpapers are printed on 80 lb. Mohawk Superfine Text. The book has a hand-sewn linen binding, ribbon bookmark, cover of Japanese book cloth over boards and tipped-in title plate.

Product name: Wooden Fountain Pen handmade In c5000 yr old Irish Bog Oak. Perfect Gift For Any Occasion: Birthday, St Patrick's Day, Fathers Day, etc.
Description:
This handmade wooden fountain pen would make a perfect gift for any occasion. It has a traditional style reminiscent of the 'Gentleman's' pens of days gone by. It is finished in Irish Bog Oak wood with 24ct gold fittings. Similar wood recovered from peat bogs has been carbon dated at between 3000 & 5000 years old. I have finished it with a blend of waxes and polishes to give a durable and long lasting protection making it suitable for daily use.
ABOUT THIS PEN:
- Features a medium/firm German made nib.
- Perfectly balanced for an exceptional writing experience.
- The pen (without cap) measures approx 5" (13 1/2 cm) long and 3/4" (2cm) at it's widest.
- This is a non-posted fountain pen (i.e. the cap is kept separate from the barrel while the pen is in use),
- This pen will come with a refillable ink piston as well as five ink cartridges in either blue or black.
- This would make a perfect gift for any occasion.
- The pen will come with guidance on use, care and storage.
- All of my pens and pencils are individually hand made. Each one is completely unique.
- Notebooks similar to the one shown can be seen at www.tanglecrafts.etsy.com 
 
DELIVERY:
I aim to post all orders the next working day.
These are Royal Mail's guidelines on delivery times:
- UK orders are generally delivered the next working day,
- overseas orders are generally delivered within 7-10 working days after postage , but can sometimes take a little longer.
I recommend that all buyers use the Shipping Upgrade Option to take advantage of the tracking facility provided by Royal Mail. Once an item is posted, I cannot be held responsible for any loss/damage/delays in post.
Customers outside the UK please check the import restrictions for your country before ordering as you may be liable for import duties/taxes etc.
CUSTOM ORDERS:
I am happy to accept custom orders. I keep a variety of timber on hand, so if you like these pens, but not this wood, why not have one specially made just for you in your own choice of timber? Or, perhaps you have own special piece of wood that you'd like a pen or pencil made from? Feel free to get in touch with me to chat about your requirements.

• TYPE OF FOLDS? 
• • Straight cut - No fold. Straight cut labels are usually sewn on all 4 sides, the top, or on
left and right side only. No extra charge for this fold.  
• • End fold - Endfold  labels are folded down on the left and right side. They are applied the
same way as straight cut labels, but have a softer edge. Sewing contractors may charge
more for this fold, so please consult them before making your ﬁnal decision. This fold does require an extra charge.
• • Loop Fold - These labels are folded in the top and bottom,usually sewn in bottom T-shirt. Loop fold labels can also be used for sleeve and hem labels.  
• • Centerfold - These labels are folded in the middle and usually sewn into a seam.
Centerfold labels can also be used for sleeve and hem labels. This fold does require an extra charge.
••  Book cover fold - These labels are folded in the middle and end fold ,  can also be used for sleeve and hem labels. usually sewn in bottom T-shirt. This fold does require an extra charge.
••  Miter Fold - With miter fold labels, the ends are folded under and up, creating a tab to be sewn into a seam. This fold does require an extra charge.
••  Manhattan Fold - Manhattan fold is just like a centerfold label, except the top of the
label is folded down, creating a flap to tuck the bottom fold into.  If you need HEM LABELS we highly recommend the manhattan fold! This fold requires an extra charge.
• NEED SIZES? custom size label Min. order 1000 labels to weave FREE SIZING into your labels ie: S,M,L etc.  
here is liting for stock size label Min.order 100pcs per size : 
http://etsy.me/1XsCo4G

• PROOFS or SAMPLES? 
You will receive a digital proof view showing the placement of your design, logo and fold. If you want an ACTUAL woven label sample of your design made prior to production, there is a 15.00 charge.
• RETURNS or REFUNDS? Refunds are happily given 100% if we have not gone to production or sampling yet. All orders are painstakingly custom made just for you. All sales are final on custom woven damask labels.
• Cancellations?
Once an order is put into production and is cancelled you will be liable for the cost of the entire order since it is totally customized to your specifications and can’t be used by anyone else.
• IMPORTANT READ ABOUT: Our Strict Disclaimer And Design Limitations Regarding Industry Standard Woven Labels.
This is industry standard for woven labels. With weaving, it is impossible to have 100% detail to match your graphic art, as these are literally stitched/woven labels and NOT printed labels.  
The size after cut and folded finished both have -2mm tolerances. The colors of yarn can have tolerances of up to15%.   please note that vertical line, horizontal line  circles, curves and slants are very tough with weaving, it will have a step to the next stitch line in the weaving process. Also, some letters may be larger, etc.   
If you need 100% matching of fine detail, no color of yarn "peeking" through a white background from yarn, you need printed labels instead of premium woven. The yarn/threads of woven labels may have different thicknesses hence limitations to some fine detail. By ordering woven labels you understand and agree with these industry standard tolerances and are approved by you the customer upon placing this order. The method of weaving labels involves moving parts and moving loom machinery and therefore the possibility of the above variances These are NOT printed labels!  While we try our best to avoid any tolerance, these tolerances above are industry standard for all woven labels.

Product name: Amethyst Ring: February birthstone ring, stacking ring for Valentines Day for wife for girlfriend, anniversary, copper, gemstone, purple
Description:
Handcrafted copper ring, featuring a row of raw Amethyst crystals (birthstone of February). The clarity of these crystals makes the ring especially lovely.
If you want earrings to match, these studs are made of the same crystals: 
https://www.etsy.com/listing/494217563/gypsy-earrings-stud-earrings-minimalist?ref=shop_home_active_3

Free shipping for any additional items purchased with this.
Store in the jewelry box with the tarnish resident tab that is provided with your order. 
The process: I start out with a handmade hammered ring, which gives the copper a lot of texture. I attach the stones to the ring, then sand the mounting to get the shape I want. The ring then goes through a really neat process called electroforming, where copper deposits onto the ring and around the base of the stones for about 12 hours. After waxing, sanding, and darkening the copper with a rich patina, the ring is finally complete! Long story short... a whole lot of time and love is put into this little beauty!

   Size check.<<< 
The outer edge of the 8mm is the size of Home Button on the iPhone. 10mm is slightly larger.  6mm slightly smaller.  
-Hoop sizes are based on wire gauge and interior diameters.
Interior diameter size options:
6mm - very tiny and may be OK for a tiny ear that is pierced close to the edge. Possible sites include daith, tragus and rook.
8mm - slightly larger and fits more people. Possible sites include nostril, helix, daith, tragus, and second lobe.
10mm - good for a piercing farther away from the edge of the ear. Possible sites include lobe, helix, septum.
These are only estimations.  Class X wants you to be happy with your purchase.  Every piercing is different so be sure to take notice of your own for proper fit as we can not offer returns due to hygienic reasons. 
-Wire 
22 gauge - Slim wire (delicate)
20 gauge - Standard wire
14K gold filled, 14k rose gold filled, or Sterling silver
Item Information:
Set of two hoops.
All of our cartilage and nose hoops are a seamless style,  twist open and close, and can be worn on any piercing.
Hoop Care - 
To extend the life of your hoops, please remove before bathing, swimming and sleeping.
Store in a dry, clean ziplock bag.
Sterling silver will tarnish over time.  To clean your hoops, add mild dishsoap to a bowl of warm water and let soak for a few minutes.  Gently use a soft cloth to remove any impurities, rinse and buff dry.
